Based on the context provided, the documentation references an [Events](#events) section in `extensions.md`, but the full event list wasn't included in the retrieved context.

However, from the **examples**, I can confirm these events are used in practice:

| Event | Source |
|---|---|
| `session_start` | `event-bus.ts`, `rpc-demo.ts` |
| `session_switch` | `rpc-demo.ts` |
| `session_before_switch` | `rpc-demo.ts` |
| `agent_start` | `06-extensions.ts` |
| `agent_end` | `06-extensions.ts` |
| `tool_call` | `06-extensions.ts`, `rpc-demo.ts` |
| `turn_start` | `rpc-demo.ts` |
| `turn_end` | `rpc-demo.ts` |
| `input` | `input-transform.ts` |

**Yes, `turn_start` is a real event.** From `examples/extensions/rpc-demo.ts`:

```typescript
pi.on("turn_start", async (_event, ctx) => {
  turnCount++;
  ctx.ui.setStatus("rpc-demo", `Turn ${turnCount} running...`);
});

pi.on("turn_end", async (_event, ctx) => {
  ctx.ui.setStatus("rpc-demo", `Turn ${turnCount} done`);
});
```

For the **complete authoritative event list**, you'd need to check the full `extensions.md` docs directly (the Events and Lifecycle Overview sections), as the full enumeration wasn't retrieved in this context.
